What Myrniidon or Dolopian, or soldier of stern Ulysses, could in telling such a tale refrain from tears? Now, too, dewy night is speeding from the sky 1 and the setting stars invite to sleep. Yet if thou hast such longing to learn our disasters‚ and in few words to hear of Troy’s last agony, though my mind shudders to remember, and has recoiled in grief, I will begin.
